Cell["\<\
The Fredkin gate was invented by Edward Fredkin for classical reversible \
computation.\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->1067943069,ExpressionUUID->"70861dcf-fd72-4a5d-989c-92d9a2fe7523"],

Cell["\<\
For classical reversible computation, it is universal in the sense that any \
logical or arithmetic operation can be constructed entirely of Fredkin gates.\
\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->168460463,ExpressionUUID->"088154e1-8f64-48be-ad79-07049ae934f4"],

Cell["The Fredkin gate is also used in the SWAP test.", "Notes",
 CellID->283622244,ExpressionUUID->"6193bbe4-0951-4715-b9cf-619bebbbf6c0"]
}, Dynamic[CurrentValue[
 EvaluationNotebook[], {TaggingRules, "Openers", "NotesSection"}, Closed]]]],

